Proposed Amendments to HB 4053 Page 2

1 sioners has by order, after public hearing, granted exemption from such
2 subsections to the individual, group, partnership, entity, association or or-
3 ganization.
4 “(6)(a) Subsection (1) of this section does not apply to a student who
5 provides emergency care or nonemergency care in this state under the
6 supervision of a qualified supervisor and as part of the clinical com-
7 ponent of an emergency medical services course:
8 “(A) Offered by a school located in this state and approved by the
9 Oregon Health Authority;
10 “(B) Offered by a school located in another state if the school meets
11 the requirements of the Higher Education Coordinating Commission
12 to qualify a student for application for licensure under this chapter;
13 or
14 “(C) Offered by a school located in another state if the course meets
15 the requirements of the emergency medical services licensing body to
16 qualify a student for application for emergency medical services
17 licensure in that state.
18 “(b) A student enrolled in a course described in this subsection may
19 use the title and initials specified in subsection (1) of this section for
20 the level of license for which the student is in training.
21 “(7) When exemption is granted under this section, any person who at-
22 tends an individual who is ill or injured or who has a disability in an am-
23 bulance may not purport to be an emergency medical services provider.”.
